#Install binaries from Bioconductor version 3.16. See tutorial DAADA2 Installation and dada2 tutorial

#Install BiocManager

if (!requireNamespace("BiocManager", quietly = TRUE))
    install.packages("BiocManager")

#Install DADA2

#BiocManager::install("dada2")

#Load the DADA2 library

library(dada2); packageVersion("dada2")
## Loading required package: Rcpp
## [1] '1.34.0'

#Set the path to fastq files

path <- "//home/brymoore/wsg_gtdb_tax/pig_microbiome/PRJNA214736" #Change me to the directory containing the fastq files(unzipped)

list.files(path)
## [1] "filtered"              "PRJNA214736_DADA2.Rmd" "SRR987438"            
## [4] "SRR987438_1.fastq"     "SRR987439"             "SRR987439_2.fastq"
# In side of the folder containing my fastq files
fnFs <- sort(list.files(path, pattern="fastq", full.names=TRUE))

sample.names <- sapply(strsplit(basename(fnFs), "_"), `[`, 1)
sample.names
## [1] "SRR987438" "SRR987439"
plotQualityProfile(fnFs[1:2])

filt_path <- file.path(path, "filtered")
dir.create(filt_path)
## Warning in dir.create(filt_path):
## '//home/brymoore/wsg_gtdb_tax/pig_microbiome/PRJNA214736/filtered' already
## exists
filtFs <- file.path(filt_path, basename(fnFs))

out <- filterAndTrim(
  fnFs, filtFs,
  truncLen = 150,     # adjust from quality plot
  maxN = 0,
  maxEE = 2,
  truncQ = 2,
  rm.phix = TRUE,
  compress = TRUE,
  multithread = TRUE
)
errF <- learnErrors(filtFs, multithread=TRUE)
## 147637350 total bases in 984249 reads from 2 samples will be used for learning the error rates.
plotErrors(errF, nominalQ=TRUE)
## Warning in scale_y_log10(): log-10 transformation introduced infinite values.

derepFs <- derepFastq(filtFs)
names(derepFs) <- sample.names
dadaFs <- dada(derepFs, err=errF, multithread=TRUE)
## Sample 1 - 555962 reads in 56398 unique sequences.
## Sample 2 - 428287 reads in 43602 unique sequences.
seqtab <- makeSequenceTable(dadaFs)
seqtab.nochim <- removeBimeraDenovo(seqtab, method="consensus", multithread=TRUE)
write.csv(seqtab.nochim,  file = "PRJNA214736_seqtab.nochim.csv", row.names = F)
